id="v.iv.vi.x-p36.2"></span>

<span id="v.iv.vi.x-p37"></span> Marcion seems to have changed *man*
into *Lord*, or rather to have omitted the <span class="Greek"><span
id="v.iv.vi.x-p37.1"></span>ἄνθρωπος</span> of the second clause,
letting the verse run thus: <span class="Greek"><span
id="v.iv.vi.x-p37.2"></span>ὁ πρῶτος ἄνθρωπος ἐκ γῆς χοϊκὁς, ὁ δεύτερος
Κύριος ἐξ οὐρανοῦ</span>. Anything to cut off all connection with the
Creator.

